Format strings use standard Go `text/template` syntax.

Available Variables:
  .player   The name of the player instance.
  .status   The playback status (e.g., Playing, Paused, Stopped).
  .title    The title of the current track.
  .artist   The artist of the current track.
  .album    The album of the current track.
  .volume   The current volume level.
  .position The current playback position in microseconds.
  .rate     The current playback rate.
  .shuffle  The current shuffle status.
  .loopStatus The current loop status.
  .activePlaylistName The name of the currently active playlist.
  .activePlaylistId   The id of the currently active playlist.
  .playlistCount      The total number of playlists.
  .trackCount         The number of tracks in the current tracklist.

  Note: Any valid metadata key (e.g., .mpris:artUrl, .xesam:audioBPM) is also available.

Custom Functions:
  lc                            Lowercase string.
  uc                            Uppercase string.
  default <fallback> <value>    Return fallback if value is empty.
  duration <value>              Format duration value.
  markup_escape <value>         HTML escape string.
  emoji <status>                Return an emoji for playback status.
  trunc <max> <value>           Truncate string to max length.
  add <a> <b>                   Add two integers.
  sub <a> <b>                   Subtract two integers.
  has_playlist <count>          Returns true if count is greater than 0.
  has_tracklist <count>         Returns true if count is greater than 0.

Examples:
  {{.ProgramName}} --format '{{ "{{ .title }}" }} by {{ "{{ .artist }}" }}' metadata
  {{.ProgramName}} --format '{{ "{{ default .title \"Unknown\" }}" }}' metadata
